caption.paragraph:
FIGURE 12.

Brachypeplus instriatus


sp. nov.

, orig. A–E: male from ACT (“Canberra… apricots”); 
A
: body, dorsal; 
B
: head, dorsal; 
C
: head and thorax, ventral; 
D
: shoulder place of elytron, dorsal; 
E
: abdominal apex, ventrolateral; F-I: male from? QLD (“in sawdust Caboolture…”); F: male anal sclerite and 
spiculum gastrale
, ventral; 
G
: tegmen, ventral; 
H
: penis trunk, dorsal; 
I
: proximal part of inner sac with armature; 
J
: female from SA (“Port Lincoln, Blackburn”); ovipositor, ventral. Scale bars: 
a
= 1.0 mm to Fig. A; 
b
= 1.0 mm to Figs B, C, E; 
с
= 0.5 mm to Fig. D; 
d
= 0.25 mm to Figs F–J.
